# Code Style Guidelines

## Overview

Our code style guidelines ensure consistency and maintainability across the codebase.

## TypeScript/JavaScript Standards

### File Organization

- One component per file
- Clear file naming (PascalCase for components)
- Logical grouping of related files
- Consistent directory structure

### Code Structure

- Function declarations using `function` keyword
- Consistent use of arrow functions for callbacks
- Clear separation of concerns
- Logical grouping of methods

### Naming Conventions

- PascalCase for components and types
- camelCase for variables and functions
- UPPER_CASE for constants
- Descriptive and meaningful names
- Prefix boolean variables with is/has/should

### Formatting

- 2 space indentation
- Single quotes for strings
- Semicolons required
- No trailing commas
- Maximum line length of 80 characters

### Component Structure

```typescript
// Imports
import { type FC } from 'react';
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';

// Types
interface Props {
  id: string;
  name: string;
}

// Component
export const MyComponent: FC<Props> = ({ id, name }) => {
  // Hooks
  const query = useQuery({ ... });

  // Handlers
  const handleClick = () => {
    // ...
  };

  // Render
  return (
    <div>
      {/* JSX */}
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Best Practices

### General

- Keep functions small and focused
- Use early returns
- Avoid nested conditionals
- Use guard clauses
- Prefer immutability

### TypeScript

- Use strict type checking
- Avoid `any` type
- Use interface for objects
- Use type for unions/intersections
- Document complex types

### React

- Use functional components
- Follow hooks rules
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use proper prop types
- Implement proper cleanup

### Testing

- Clear test descriptions
- One assertion per test
- Proper test isolation
- Consistent testing patterns
- Meaningful test coverage

## Tools and Enforcement

### ESLint

- Strict mode enabled
- React plugin rules
- TypeScript rules
- Import sorting
- Error prevention

### Prettier

- Automatic formatting
- Consistent style
- IDE integration
- Pre-commit hooks
- CI/CD checks

